      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "also, I noticed that in several places we use `ARM_SHANI`. this might be a bit misleading, since as far as I know `SHA-NI` is Intel/x86 related and has nothing to do with ARM.  `x86_shani` makes sense, but I’m not sure `arm_shani` is the right term here.\r\n\r\nnot sure if it is worth changing since the term is already used in many places, but happy to follow up with a PR if we want to clean that up.",
